.TH sHell 1 "April 2022"
.SH NAME
.B Simple sHell \- takes commands and execute them
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./sHell
[COMMAND] [OPTION/FILES]
.sp
.B echo
[COMMAND][FILE] | ./sHell
.SH DESCRIPTION
The 
.B simple sHell
is an interpreter that executes commands from the input or from other file.
.SS Overview
The simple_shell is a command that reads lines from either a file
and generally executes other commands.
.SH INITIALIZATION
 To use the simple sHell the user needs to compile using: gcc
 The simple sHell will compile with the following:
 gcc -Wall -Wextra -Werror -pedantic *.c -o sHell

.SH BULTINS

env - prints the enviornment variables

exit - quits the program.

Ctrl+C - Implementation of signal when entering ^C

.SH EXAMPLE
.sp
.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
#Cisfun$ /bin/ls
 AUTHORS    elprompt.c    sshell.h
 README.md  execute_cmd.c  sHell

#Cisfun$ /bin/pwd
  /home/simple_shell

#Cisfun$ a
  ./sHell: No such file or directory


#Cisfun$ exit
  Sucessful exit!
.sp
.SH NON-INTERACTIVE MODE
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./sHell
.sp
sHell main.c shell.c test_ls_2
.sp


.SH REPORTING BUGS
Keep in mind this is still a very early WIP prototype and may not fully work as intented in every case

